	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002269_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 <p>RELATING TO HIS &quot;NARRATIVE OF AN EXPEDITION TO <lb/>ZAMBESI - 1858/64&quot;</p> across top--><!--Hand 02 52 top left--><!--Hand 03 63007 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right">22 April 1865</p><!--red printed address on notepaper<p rend="right">NEWSTEAD ABBEY,</p>
<p rend="right">MANSFIELD.</p>
<p rend="right">NOTTS.</p>--><!--end of printed address-->
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Man Alive - that 
<lb/>terrible 600!! pages 
<lb/>and I have been 
<lb/>toiling like a galley 
<lb/>slave to bring it 
<lb/>up to 450 and 
<lb/>all the while fearing 
<lb/>to think of my 
<lb/>men &amp; steamer 
<lb/>waiting for me 
<lb/>at Bombay &amp; 
<lb/>one of them dead 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002269_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>I have spread it 
<lb/>so evenly over the 
<lb/>whole <hi rend="underline">I don't see</hi>
<lb/>at present what 
<lb/>I can leave out 
<lb/>save the "conclusion" 
<lb/>and "appendix" 
<lb/>I put in a great 
<lb/>many parts with 
<lb/>great care &amp; 
<lb/>thought only to 
<lb/>lengthen it, but 
<lb/>we shall see 
<lb/>what can be 
<lb/>done. I shall 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002269_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>write to Oswell today 
<lb/>about it. Is it 
<lb/>absolutely necessary 
<lb/>to curtail more 
<lb/>than what I have 
<lb/>mentioned. The 
<lb/>"Conclusion" gives 
<lb/>a summary of 
<lb/>results and the 
<lb/>book would be 
<lb/>the better of it</p>
<lb/><p>I shall go up 
<lb/>to town about Tuesday 
<lb/>next, and will 
<lb/>see you about this 
<lb/>which has struck 
<lb/>"me all of a heap" </p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002269_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Till then believe me 
<lb/>My Dear Cooke</p>
<lb/><p>Yours ever</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Speke has 650 pages 
<lb/>or 612 to end of his 
<lb/>narrative. might 
<lb/>not Milton be a little 
<lb/>more sparing with 
<lb/>his <unclear cert="low">Mss</unclear></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Some of the drawings 
<lb/>are Wallers &amp; some 
<lb/>Mellers. I shall tell 
<lb/>you which is which 
<lb/>Have you a receipt for 
<lb/>Baines drawings</p>
			
